#CONTENT:
This java command line application aligns Next-Generation Sequencing (NGS) reads
to a reference sequence, by a fast k-mer matching and removes indels, causing
frame shifts. In addition, only specific regions can be considered.

#PREREQUISITES TO RUN:
 - JDK 7 (http://jdk7.java.net/)
 - Get latest version: https://github.com/armintoepfer/QuasiAlign/downloads

#RUN:
 java -jar QuasiAlign.jar -i libCase102.sff -g referenceGenome.fasta
 or
 java -jar QuasiAlign.jar -i libCase102.fasta -g referenceGenome.fasta

#USE / SHOW HELP:
 java -jar QuasiAlign.jar

#Extract reads of particular regions
 java -jar QuasiAlign.jar -i libCase102.sff -g referenceGenome.fasta -r 342-944,1239-3889

